text:
hello,
I think we properly bonded over late-night walks in second year summers (miss those puppies outside chick blast though). since then I have always enjoyed your company especially the random late-night walks. you were the one person to confide in for all my worries, from those silly relationship dramas (I hope this remains confidential under homie-homie privilege) to more serious academic decisions. I remember you probably hitting (ง︡'-'︠)ง on me during 3rd year, but then you were always like that, I guess. 
Always loved your not-taking-a-shit attitude (sorry goa mein chilla diya that one fine morning). Hoping that cloud of indecisiveness settles down so that you do not think about the road not taken. Thank you for your support (twice, that is), for being in touch with me during the lockdown and making me realise the importance of staying connected. Always looking forward to the weekly calls and more late-night walks ( ͡ᵔ ͜ʖ ͡ᵔ) 

P.S bata na uss prof ko mail karu ya nahi?
author: Neelesh Kumar Vij

text:
Yoo Yash aka dalla, yeet. T.
EE381 lab mein kitna torture kiya tumne, but then amlost saara kaam bhi tumne kiya tha. You are the epitome of completing a task to its finest details. Where I gave up ki yeh nahi likh raha kitne hi marks kaat dega prof, tum 2 extra para likh ke aate the lmao.
Thank you for making me realise not to be a campaigne, for helping me out in my associate head tenure, for all the notes and assignment solutions, and also for all other things that I cannot remember now.
